description: March 2019 - Having fun climbing outdoors in the cold! Cold is when the rock has the highest friction, it's the best time to send some projects!
April 2019 - V9 project Chain reaction. This move is so beautiful to me! But this project has a fear factor as there is a large rock directly behind me; not a very fun fall…
Aug 2019 - Climbed the silo at Allez Up in Montreal - gave the best views of the city

March 2019 - Sent my first V10 (Closed Eye Visuals) - I sent my highest bouldering grade attempted outdoors which may not have been a V10 for me, largely due to the fact that I just found new painful micro-crimps to make my way up the boulder.
March 2016 - First time competing for University Bouldering Series and managed to make second place in the intermediate females category!
August 2018 - Having so much fun outdoor bouldering!
Jan 2015 - Where it all started - my passion for climbing began in the local university bouldering room.
At a climbing gym in Toronto - I think this was a V3 problem, but I was quite proud to be sitting on top of the mushroom-looking hold
Attractive dragon climb for bouldering at a higher-than-normal height
